A vehicle was recovered by the Limpopo police before it could be completely smuggled into Zimbabwe across the Limpopo river.It is believed that the suspects were using donkeys to pull the car across the river when police arrived on time after the donkeys apparently were not able to pull the car through the sand.&#8220;A Mercedes Benz sedan C220 was intercepted just in time before disappearing into Zimbabwe,&#8221; said Police Spokesperson LT Col Moatshe Ngoepe.He added, &#8220;The suspects fled into the bushes towards Zimbabwe&#8221;.Police are set to continue with the investigation.-TNA Reporter